Of conduct, possession was always taken  as  evidence  giving  rise  to  a ç
presumption of title.
Persons coming from respectable families, deeply religious by temperament ç
and hence devoted to truth, who were straightforward  were  considered  as ç
reliable witnesses.
Interesting descriptions of an untruthful witness are given. Some ç
of them are: shifting the position constantly; licking the corner ç
of one's own lips; sweat on the forehead; change of colour of the ç
countenance; faltering speech; contradictory statements.
