By thus depicting the goddess of learning and wisdom, Hinduism has ç
elevated all fields of knowledge to divine levels.
For a Hindu, his art has originated from God himself. And, his art ç
is also the best means of worshipping God!
Hindu art has several facets: drawing and painting; sculpture; dance ç
and drama; music.
Actually these arts are sometimes enumerated as 64! Some of them, ç
for instance, are: floral designs, preparing various kinds of beds, ç
magic, culinary arts, reading from books, carpentry, goat-fighting, ç
composing poems, physical exercises, hair dressing and so on.
But, the five streams mentioned above are highly developed and hence ç
